The Org Difference features uses a Last Modified Date returned by the Salesforce API to calculate differences. Whilst this difference calculation is quicker than the Snapshot Difference feature (see below), you do not see the exact changes made. Creating a deployment from the Org Difference feature is more precise because the individual metadata can be selected (e.g. 1 validation rule or custom field on the Account), rather than the entire file Salesforce returns. An understanding of the Metadata API is advised here, as not all changes in Salesforce update the Last Modified Date (e.g. changes to picklist values will not update the picklist's last modified date).

The Snapshot Difference feature allows the XML differences to be displayed. Copado is using Git to calculate the differences in the XML files returned by Salesforce and highlight these to you. This means you can see what has changes (e.g. in a custom field or a validation rule on the Account) have been made. However, creating a deployment from here will add the entire account object to the deployment (a file based deployment), where you thereby deploy all related metadata, such as all validation rules, custom fields, list views etc... The Org Difference feature is different in this respect as it deploys individual metadata items (e.g. the 1 validation rule or custom field you selected on the Account).

Deployment of Profiles using the MetaData API. During deployment, profiles are automatically cleaned, removing any components that do not exist in the destination Org. Some limitations are imposed by the API. For details, please review the MetaData API documentation. “Full” Profiles are called like that because we do a full describe of your org, to make sure we included every single property of the profiles. Basic profile deployment, can be done using a Metadata Step, and profile’s properties deployed will be relative to the set of Metadata included in the same step.
Deployment of MetaData components. For a complete list of deployable meta data components please refer to the Salesforce MetaData API documentation.

Deployment of full language translations. Selecting a language to be deployed will deploy all translated values for that language for all Salesforce components (not just those included in the deployment). Every single translatable piece that is translated will be deployed (including everything in the Translation Workbench and all that are NOT part of it as well, like labels, tabs, object names, etc).
